reviewText: The movies included in this collection are masterpieces from Hollywood's Golden Era.I used to collect this type of films in their 16 mm editions many years ago and would pay $150 to $200 each when I could find them. Now, many of them are included in a very good definition in this magnificent collection at an unbelievably low price.I am now using the space of my old 16mm film collection for a more useful purpose.
summary: It is amazing that this collection of masterpieces is available at such low price

reviewText: Why the marketing geniuses at Millcreek Entertainment chose to put Fred Astaire on the cover, and call this 4-Disc, 20 title set "Classic Movie Musicals" is beyond me. Had they understood the cult staus enjoyed by WWII-era B-pictures, this set of public domain gems would not have hit the bargain bins upon its 2010 release."Classic Movie Musicals" actually contains a very tasty cross-section of late 1930s-'40s Swing and Race (black) genre films from the archives of the Library of Congress.If you love big bands, jitterbugs, and the more obscure genre of all-black "race" films, you won't want to miss this excellent collection. You can actually track 1940s black swing as it evolved into Rock & Roll. And for the insanely low price of under $5.00 for 26 hours of classic musical B-pictures - well, you'd be L-7 to pass this collection by.TITLES: All-American Co-Ed, Black Tights, Career Girl, Doll Face, The Duke Is Tops, The Fabulous Dorseys, Hi-De-Ho, Hi Diddle Diddle, Killer Diller, Let's Go Collegiate, Minstrel Man, Paradise In Harlem, Private Buckaroo, Reet Petite And Gone, Royal Wedding, Second Chorus, Stage Door Canteen, Till The Clouds Roll By, Trocadero, Up In The Air.FEATURED: Tommy & Jimmy Dorsey, Cab Calloway, Harry James, Louis Jordan, Benny Goodman, Nat Cole Trio, Lena Horne, Andrews Sisters, Cats & The Fiddle, Count Basie, Edgar Bergan & Charlie McCarthy, Jackie "Moms" Mabley, Sheldon Leonard, Butterfly McQueen, Shemp Howard, Kathryn Hepburn, Mary Wickes... (and yes, Frank Sinatra, Judy Garland, and Fred Astair are all in there, too.
summary: FORGET THE TITLE - THIS DVD IS A 10+

reviewText: I grew up listening to musicals, big bands, and symphonies.  My father was a musician, composer, and band leader in his younger years (born in 1904)  Watching these bands, especially the older ones are fun and I get to see a piece of his life as a result.  There is quite a variety enclosed .

reviewText: I don't actually own this particular set, but I do own the Classic Musicals 50 Movie Pack which contains all the same 20 movies on this plus 30 more.  Obviously not all of these movies can be a "Singin' In the Rain," but what a delight to view so many more obscure films from the same era.  And if your interested in the set of 50, it's listed on Amazon under the name "Musicals Classics 50 Movie Pack Collection" and at this writing is only $4.50 more than this set of 20.

reviewText: Unless "classic" just means old.  I do love old movies and when I had TV I watched a lot of old movies.  I also love musicals, but I was sorely disappointed with this collection.  There are 4 discs of movies in the package and of all the so-called classics, I had only heard of or previously seen 4 of them.  I suppose this is not a terribly bad value for the price, but I already have "Royal Wedding" on another disc featuring Fred Astaire, and I wouldn't have purchased this set just to get the Dorsey Brothers film.  I think this set would be a good buy for students of Black History in the Arts.
summary: Not my idea of classic

reviewText: This set is worth twice the price simply for Black Tights. Such wonderful dancing and choreography...Zizi Jeanmaire, Cyd Charisse, Roland Petit, Moira Shearer....wow!  Some of the films are real turkeys, but even they are fun as they give you a chance to see some performers like Butterfly McQueen and Frances Langford.  If only all studios had had the production values of MGM and Fox.....still you can't go wrong in buying this, especially considering the price.  Royal Wedding has not been remastered in this set, and if you are buying for that consider getting the remastered version separately.
summary: Some Real Jewels In This Set
